# 4. 思い描くフィナーレは

Airi: This is your carnival's final stop...?
Tsukasa: B-But why? You've been able to put smiles on the faces of so many...
Inuyama: Fortunately, yes. It's a moving sight to behold.
Inuyama: However, as you can see, I'm not young... Traveling around from place to place takes its toll.
Nene: Oh...
Inuyama: But I'm satisfied. I started this carnival with the dream of putting smiles on the faces of people all over.
Inuyama: And I've successfully accomplished that.
Mizuki: People all over...
Inuyama: Yes. Even today, I got to see all these guests smile and laugh. That includes you kids.
Inuyama: And I couldn't be happier.
Tsukasa: Mr. Inuyama...
Tsukasa: I see... It is unfortunate to hear that such a wonderful carnival is going to be closing its gates... But I also believe that you've made a large number of people very happy.
Tsukasa: That obviously includes me!
Inuyama: Ah, thank you.
Tsukasa: I know. Would it be alright if I asked you when your final day is?
Inuyama: Huh?
Tsukasa: We'd like to come visit again if possible!
Mizuki: Yeah, we were just talking about coming back!
Inuyama: Haha. You did say that.
Inuyama: The final day is two weeks from now. You're all more than welcome to visit if you're free then.
Nene: Two weeks from now... We don't have practice then.
Airi: I'm also free. So, let's all come back together, the four of us!
Tsukasa: Agreed! We shall return to this carnival and witness what is surely going to be a spectacular finale!
Inuyama: ...!
Inuyama: A spectacular finale...
Nyantaro: Meooow...
Nene: Is something wrong, Mr. Inuyama...?
Inuyama: No, it's nothing serious. It's just...
Inuyama: If only we could do that show... Then we'd be able to give this carnival the send-off it deserves.
Mizuki: That show?
Tsukasa: Would it be possible for you to tell us more...?
Inuyama: ...
Inuyama: So, to celebrate the opening of this carnival, we put on a show for the first week. The staff and I came up with it together...
Inuyama: But we'd never done anything like that before in our lives. Through trial and error, we wrote a script, designed all the costumes and whatnot. It was quite an ordeal...
Inuyama: That being said...
Inuyama: When we actually put on the show, all that pain suddenly disappeared.
Inuyama: The audience clearly enjoyed our show. I saw the carnival guests all smiling and laughing. It was the moment I realized that this is how dreams are made.
Inuyama: I'm never going to forget that sensation I felt. Which is why...
Tsukasa: Which is why this show means so much to you all...
Inuyama: Yes, and I was hoping that we could put it on one last time before the carnival closes for good... But we can't...
Airi: Wait, why not?
Inuyama: Not only were we not able to find a full copy of the script, the costumes also need repairs. Those and a few other factors brought us to the conclusion that it won't be possible.
Inuyama: You might think we should simply put on a brand-new show... But only that show from our beginnings would hold any real meaning as this carnival's final spectacle.
Inuyama: So, we've given up on doing one.
Airi: That's so unfortunate...
Inuyama: I'm sorry. I shouldn't be talking about something so negative to a group of guests.
Tsukasa: No, I was the one who asked. More importantly...
Tsukasa: If you don't feel comfortable with this, Mr. Inuyama, I'll understand... But would you allow me to put on this show?
Tsukasa: I've actually been a cast member at an amusement park, and I was incredibly touched by your story just now.
Tsukasa: I understand what you meant when you talked about wanting to see everyone smile and not being able to forget that sensation you felt.
Tsukasa: So, if possible, I'd like to help out.
Inuyama: Tenma...
Airi: Me too... I'd also like to lend a hand.
Airi: Like Tenma said, we made a lot of great memories here today...
Airi: You've made a lot of people smile up until now, Mr. Inuyama. So, I want to make sure you're smiling wide at the finale!
Inuyama: I appreciate the kind offer... But as I just mentioned, we don't even have a full copy of the script.
Inuyama: And the costumes really are in tatters...
Tsukasa: I'll do something about the script. I can try to reconstruct the story based on everything you can remember!
Mizuki: As for the costumes, I might be able to help. If you have pictures or any other references for what they used to look like, I should be able to restore them!
Airi: I'm not as good as Mizuki here, but I also know my way around a sewing machine.
Nene: Umm... I can't help fix the costumes or anything...
Nene: But I can help out as a member of the cast.
Tsukasa: All of you...!
Tsukasa: We promise to make you and the guests all smile, Mr. Inuyama.
Tsukasa: So, please... Would you let us do your show?
Inuyama: Thank you all very much... If you're willing to go this far...
Inuyama: ...
Inuyama: I know it's beyond unreasonable to ask people who I just met to help me with this. But...
Inuyama: If it means getting to experience that feeling again...
Inuyama: Alright... Would you help an old man make his dream come true?
Tsukasa: ...! Yes, of course!
Tsukasa: In the name of putting smiles on you and all the guests, Mr. Inuyama...
Tsukasa: We promise to make this show a success!
